==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unbay
<hw>Un*bay"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>bay</ets> to dam.]</ety> <def>To free from the
restraint of anything that surrounds or incloses; to let loose; to
open.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I ought . . . to <qex>unbay</qex> the current of my passion.</q>
<rj><qau>Norris.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unbe</ent>⟦br⟧
